HB 51 Re-Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Villio
Abstract: Prohibits post-conviction bail for a defendant who is convicted of an aggravated
offense against a victim who is a minor.
Present constitution provides for the right to bail.
Proposed constitutional amendment retains present constitution.
Proposed constitutional amendment provides that a person convicted of an aggravated
offense, as defined by present law (R.S. 15:541), against a minor is not eligible for any post-
conviction bail.
Provides for submission of the proposed amendment to the voters at the statewide election
to be held Nov. 3, 2026.
(Adds Const. Art. I, §18(C))
